<recipe>
<title>
Banana Split Dessert Pizza
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 16 oz. tube sugar cookie dough
8 oz. whipped cream cheese
1/4 c. granulated sugar
4 oz. strawberries sliced
1 banana sliced
M&M
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Gently press cookie dough into pizza pan.
Bake 15-20 minutes, or until lightly browned at the edges and set in the middle.
Let crust cool to room temperature.
Once crust is at room temperature, beat together cream cheese and sugar until well-combined.
Spread over cookie crust leaving a small crust edge.
Top with sliced strawberries, sliced banana, and M&Ms.
</instructions>
</recipe>
